1
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:29,160
Leaving behind Milan’s urban charm,

2
00:01:29,160 --> 00:01:30,600
the Departure Family heads to their next stop:

3
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:33,360
they arrive at the southern foothills
of the Alps,

4
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:34,160
on the shores of Lake Como.

5
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:38,280
Along the lakeside stand many

6
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:41,440
ancient villas from the Renaissance.

7
00:01:41,440 --> 00:01:43,120
The lake and mountains here

8
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:44,560
blend with Italian style,

9
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,680
coming together perfectly into

10
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,800
the scenery of countless dreams.

11
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:50,280
Along the shore

12
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:52,320
are many sailing schools.

13
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:54,040
Thanks to its changeable winds,

14
00:01:54,040 --> 00:01:57,480
Lake Como is a perfect place to sail.

15
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,400
For many years,

16
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:01,040
amid these lakes and mountains,

17
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:03,520
countless thrilling

18
00:02:03,520 --> 00:02:04,600
spy legends have unfolded.

19
00:02:10,199 --> 00:02:12,480
So the Special Agent Academy

20
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:14,280
has set its trials here.

21
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:16,400
Eight outstanding reserve agents

22
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,320
Eight outstanding reserve agents

23
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:18,440
have gathered here

24
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:21,880
to experience a top agent’s life.

25
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,120
They will soon cut through the mist,

26
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:27,520
flying by seaplane across the lake,

27
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:30,520
then taking a boat to the Special
Agent Academy.

28
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:34,440
They have only one goal:

29
00:02:34,760 --> 00:02:35,920
to pass every test.

30
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:36,760
Slow down.

31
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:37,440
Get on.

32
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:38,240
Time to close the net.

33
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:41,000
To vie for the Excellent Agent Badge.

34
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:47,600
So beautiful.

35
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:55,440
Really amazing.

36
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:56,600
Hey, there’s a tractor.

37
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:00,760
What a weird thing to notice.

38
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:03,120
All these planes don’t attract you,

39
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:05,280
but the tractor does.

40
00:03:05,880 --> 00:03:08,240
You in just trousers won’t do,
it’s too cold.

41
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:09,280
I spend winters in Beijing.

42
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:10,600
I’ve never worn thermal pants.

43
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,800
Do you wear thermals in Qiqihar
in winter?

44
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:14,400
I wear wool pants.

45
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,440
Can I go to the bathroom now?

46
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:20,000
Will there be time?

47
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:20,960
There’s one at the airport.

48
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:24,240
You two get on first, hurry.

49
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,600
If you two don’t get on now,

50
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:27,120
I’ll poop my pants, hurry!

51
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:41,320
Today he’s walking

52
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:42,320
the most naturally ever.

53
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:45,000
He’s never been natural
since birth.

54
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:47,800
Even nursing as a baby
he posed like this.

55
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:02,000
William.

56
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:17,720
Don’t fall off, bro.

57
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,480
And you still say

58
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,560
he’s never been natural?

59
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:31,880
So handsome.

60
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:43,720
Wearing a “bulletproof vest.”

61
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:46,800
The Super Model from Dandong
is here.

62
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:50,600
From Dandong, huh.

63
00:05:08,080 --> 00:05:08,760
Hurry up then.

64
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:09,720
Jingyu.

65
00:05:10,320 --> 00:05:10,920
Bing—

66
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:12,280
Brother Bing.

67
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:13,400
Brother Bing!

68
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:17,000
Xu Jiang!

69
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,840
Xu Jiang!

70
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:20,120
Xu Jinjiang!

71
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,040
Xu Jiang!

72
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,280
Xu Jiang!

73
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:28,560
Xu Jiang!

74
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:34,320
Welcome, everyone, to

75
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:34,840
Lake Como.

76
00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:36,360
the seaplane sightseeing site.

77
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:38,920
As special agents,

78
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:39,920
you must master

79
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:41,680
driving skills for many vehicles.

80
00:05:41,680 --> 00:05:44,120
Next comes your first test

81
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:45,160
as Special Agents.

82
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,080
Piloting aircraft.

83
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:47,880
The Lake Como seaplanes

84
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:49,560
are among the oldest

85
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,320
seaplane operators worldwide.

86
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:53,800
Each plane takes two trainees.

87
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:54,840
The front trainee

88
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:56,520
can try simulated flying.

89
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:57,080
You can all

90
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:58,000
form your own teams.

91
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,240
No accidents in five hundred years.

92
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,040
I still won’t go.

93
00:06:03,280 --> 00:06:04,360
I’ll just ride a boat alone.

94
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,600
A one-man solo show for me.

95
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:09,000
Two steering wheels!

96
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:10,560
I’ll fly.

97
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:12,160
You fly.

98
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:12,800
You fly.

99
00:06:12,800 --> 00:06:13,480
You don’t want to sit there?

100
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,200
Then you fly.

101
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,160
You want to fly?

102
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,320
If you fly, I’ll sit in back.

103
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:20,240
You two, let the captain sit back.

104
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,000
You two, you two, come on.

105
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:23,760
You each fly for a bit.

106
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:25,440
Captain in back, they’ll fly.

107
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:27,600
We start with a full spin cycle.

108
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:31,560
A spin cycle.

109
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:33,880
Even the captain’s speaking Chinese.

110
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:34,880
Let me off.

111
00:06:37,120 --> 00:06:38,240
Then I’ll sit in the back.

112
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:38,880
Okay.

113
00:06:42,160 --> 00:06:42,560
Thanks.

114
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,320
Hello.

115
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:44,560
Let’s go.

116
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:45,240
Nice to meet you.

117
00:06:45,600 --> 00:06:46,520
Nice to meet you, too.

118
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:49,000
Why’s it looped round my neck?

119
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,040
Okay.

120
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,360
Let’s take off.

121
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:55,000
Let’s go.

122
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:55,800
Let’s go.

123
00:06:56,840 --> 00:06:57,640
Bye.

124
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,400
That nervous look on An Yu’s face

125
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,800
is still impossible to hide.

126
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,920
We won’t just plunge down, right?

127
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:27,040
It can float on the water.

128
00:07:29,760 --> 00:07:32,360
Now we wait for the engine.

129
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:32,720
Okay.

130
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,120
Okay.

131
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:33,800
Okay.

132
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:36,320
About five minutes.

133
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:36,760
Yes.

134
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:39,280
We wait for the temp to rise.

135
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,680
Then we can fly.

136
00:07:41,680 --> 00:07:43,480
So this is very safe, right?

137
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,400
Yes.

138
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:47,360
He needs the engine

139
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,440
to warm up first.

140
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:49,400
Takes five minutes.

141
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:52,080
They think this is it.

142
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,560
They think we’re already flying.

143
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:58,680
When are they actually flying?

144
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,760
Or is this just…

145
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:00,320
…all there is?

146
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:01,160
Using it as a boat.

147
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:02,640
Just bobbing along like this.

148
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,120
I’m a bit nervous.

149
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,800
What are you nervous about?

150
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,160
Daxi,

151
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,560
your fate is now

152
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,320
in my hands.

153
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:13,960
Okay.

154
00:08:23,320 --> 00:08:24,440
So smooth!

155
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,240
We’ve taken off!

156
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:34,520
Nice job, An Yu!

157
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:35,720
How’s the experience?

158
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:37,280
Amazing.

159
00:08:41,039 --> 00:08:42,360
Beautiful.

160
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:51,600
This is awesome.

161
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:54,760
I’ll sit in the back.

162
00:08:54,760 --> 00:08:55,440
Bro, you sit in front.

163
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,200
Okay.

164
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:57,240
Hello.

165
00:08:57,240 --> 00:08:58,040
Nice to see you.

166
00:08:58,360 --> 00:08:59,320
Nice to see you, too.

167
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:00,240
We’re off, bro.

168
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:01,640
Let’s take off, just us two.

169
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:06,760
Here in Como,

170
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:09,560
planes aren’t always faster than cars.

171
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,360
these “big brains” here…

172
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:18,400
We’re airborne.

173
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:20,720
Reach out your hand.

174
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:21,240
Okay.

175
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:21,880
Okay.

176
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:24,680
Turn left.

177
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:31,240
We’ll head back in one minute.

178
00:09:37,160 --> 00:09:38,840
Are you flying it now, bro?

179
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:55,280
Xiao Hu’s plane is on the left.

180
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:56,120
Really?

181
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:56,400
Yeah.

182
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:58,480
This is so beautiful.

183
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,880
You can try flying it.

184
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:02,880
Can I?

185
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:08,800
We’re landing.

186
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:10,440
We should be landing now.

187
00:10:14,920 --> 00:10:16,280
Right now we’re using

188
00:10:16,280 --> 00:10:17,440
a spiral descent method.

189
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:20,120
It makes the weightless feeling

190
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,240
much less intense.

191
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:21,600
Relax.

192
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,160
Everything’s under my control.

193
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:27,520
You think I’m stupid, An Yu?

194
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,920
Take both hands off the yoke for a bit.

195
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:35,600
You can keep them off, it’s fine.

196
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:37,880
All done.

197
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,600
We’re heading back.

198
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:40,480
We’re heading back.

199
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:42,080
Watch your head.

200
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:42,640
Okay.

201
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:43,760
Okay.

202
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:44,560
Okay.

203
00:10:45,120 --> 00:10:46,080
And we’ve arrived.

204
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:48,680
This is the transfer point.

205
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,080
Mind your head, watch the door.

206
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:52,440
Thanks.

207
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:53,480
Fun?

208
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,080
It was insanely fun.

209
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,840
Why didn’t you ride?

210
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:59,040
I’m a bit afraid of heights.

211
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:03,360
Now we’ll take a boat to Lake Como,

212
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:05,440
to the Special Agent Academy opposite.

213
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:06,480
Let’s get on the boat.

214
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,440
Okay, thank you.

215
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:09,720
As a top special agent,

216
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:10,800
once you’ve mastered aircraft,

217
00:11:10,800 --> 00:11:13,360
next is getting used to watercraft.

218
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,040
The one open at the back.

219
00:11:19,040 --> 00:11:19,640
Open-top.

220
00:11:19,880 --> 00:11:21,160
The sun’s a bit strong here.

221
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:21,880
Come over here.

222
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:22,160
Not afraid of the sun.

223
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:22,800
I like the sun.

224
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:23,440
Yeah?

225
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:25,440
Because he needs more calcium.

226
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:26,280
Yeah.

227
00:11:26,680 --> 00:11:27,680
Sit here. This spot’s perfect.

228
00:11:29,120 --> 00:11:30,120
Yeah, that’s the spot.

229
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,280
Very nice.

230
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:33,280
Very nice.

231
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:42,080
Look, it’s gorgeous behind us.

232
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:49,000
William’s already in character.

233
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:49,800
William.

234
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:51,480
Feels like this boat is yours.

235
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:55,680
Even the photographers came.

236
00:11:55,680 --> 00:11:57,040
I won’t pose, I’ll shoot you two.

237
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:58,200
From here it really looks great.

238
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:58,480
Yeah.

239
00:11:58,480 --> 00:11:59,280
This angle’s so-so right now.

240
00:11:59,280 --> 00:12:00,160
I’m not going.

241
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:00,720
Looks amazing.

242
00:12:01,600 --> 00:12:02,080
Go on, shoot.

243
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:02,480
You take mine.

244
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:02,840
It’s gone.

245
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:03,720
I’ll shoot for you.

246
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,160
Come.

247
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:04,560
The sun’s gone past.

248
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:05,560
An Yu.

249
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:06,720
I’m not coming.

250
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:07,640
You take my photo.

251
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:10,280
Can’t even talk him into one more.

252
00:12:11,280 --> 00:12:12,320
Teng, heads up.

253
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,360
He’s ruining the whole view.

254
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,400
Looks so good.

255
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:22,920
Come on.

256
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:29,120
Looks so good.

257
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:32,040
Let me give you a new angle.

258
00:12:35,600 --> 00:12:36,160
Okay.

259
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:37,880
Your jawline’s popping, bro.

260
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:45,800
This shot works too.

261
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:47,480
This one’s not bad either.

262
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:49,120
Did you take the one that failed

263
00:12:49,120 --> 00:12:49,840
just now and enlarge it?

264
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:50,840
No.

265
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:52,520
I’ve got a solid foundation myself.

266
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:53,880
It’s mainly because the base is solid.

267
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:56,600
Come on.

268
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:56,960
You, come here.

269
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:02,400
This angle looks good.

270
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:06,880
You look damn powerful here.

271
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:07,680
Just don’t know where it is.

272
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:11,480
You color-graded it?

273
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:13,440
This one’s got to be in black and white.

274
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:15,320
Feels like the boss just passed away.

275
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:19,240
How much?

276
00:13:21,400 --> 00:13:22,040
You want it?

277
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:22,960
Fifty.

278
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:23,360
Okay.

279
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:24,360
Okay.

280
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:26,600
That’s way better than what I took.

281
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,440
Cleared two hundred fifty today.

282
00:13:30,440 --> 00:13:31,320
One fifty and one hundred.

283
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:40,000
Let’s go.

284
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:40,760
Let’s go, bro.

285
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:46,640
Banged my head.

286
00:13:47,160 --> 00:13:49,880
Which tough guy exits like that, huh?

287
00:13:52,240 --> 00:13:53,480
So beautiful.

288
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:56,880
Welcome to my home in Italy.

289
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:57,600
Nice.

290
00:13:58,560 --> 00:14:00,400
Your home in Italy.

291
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:01,080
This is…

292
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:02,680
This is a tree.

293
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:05,120
Is this your tree?

294
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,000
